},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَفْتَنُونَ","in_corpus":true,"count":3,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَفْتِنَّ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَفْتَنَّ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"فَتَنّا","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"فَتَنْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَفْتِن","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَفْتِن","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"فُتِنّا","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"فُتِنْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَفْتَن","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَفْتَن","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"}],"frequency_in_corpus":36,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَتَنَ","root":"فتن","pos":"V","occurrence_count":23},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n32969","n32970"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw into temptation, to lead astray","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"يَا بَنِي آدَمَ لَا يَفْتِنَنَّكُمُ الشَّيْطَانُ","english":"O children of Adam, let not Satan tempt you"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw into temptation, to lead astray; to enchant, to captivate, to charm, to bewitch; to seduce","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to afflict, to test, to try","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"أَوَلَا يَرَوْنَ أَنَّهُمْ يُفْتَنُونَ فِي كُلِّ عَامٍ مَّرَّةً أَوْ مَرَّتَيْنِ ثُمَّ لَا يَتُوبُونَ وَلَا هُمْ يَذَّكَّرُونَ","english":"Do they not see that they are tried every year once or twice but then they do not repent nor do they remember?"},{"text":"وَلَقَدْ فَتَنَّا سُلَيْمَانَ وَأَلْقَيْنَا عَلَى كُرْسِيِّهِ جَسَدًا ثُمَّ أَنَابَ","english":"And We certainly tried Solomon and placed on his throne a body; then he returned."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to persecute, to victimize, to oppress; to torture (in order to forcibly convert or impose a particular ideology, for example)","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"فَمَا آمَنَ لِمُوسَى إِلَّا ذُرِّيَّةٌ مِّن قَوْمِهِ عَلَى خَوْفٍ مِّن فِرْعَوْنَ وَمَلَئِهِمْ أَن يَفْتِنَهُمْ وَإِنَّ فِرْعَوْنَ لَعَالٍ فِي الْأَرْضِ وَإِنَّهُ لَمِنَ الْمُسْرِفِينَ","english":"But no one believed Moses, except youths among his people, for fear of the Pharaoh and his establishment that they would persecute them. And indeed, the Pharaoh was high [and ascendant] within the land, and indeed, he was of the transgressors."},{"text":"إِنَّ الَّذِينَ فَتَنُوا الْمُؤْمِنِينَ وَالْمُؤْمِنَاتِ ثُمَّ لَمْ يَتُوبُوا فَلَهُمْ عَذَابُ جَهَنَّمَ وَلَهُمْ عَذَابُ الْحَرِيقِ","english":"Indeed, those who have tortured the believing men and women and then have not repented will have the punishment of Hell, and they will have the punishment of the Burning Fire."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to burn, to roast","tags":["rare","transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"يَوْمَ هُمْ عَلَى النَّارِ يُفْتَنُونَ / ذُوقُوا فِتْنَتَكُمْ هَٰذَا الَّذِي كُنتُم بِهِ تَسْتَعْجِلُونَ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to burn, to roast; to melt, to smelt","tags":["rare","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"huisache, Vachellia farnesiana","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of فِتْنَة (fitna)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ف ت ن (f t n). Cognate with Mehri [script needed] (fetōn), Ge'ez ፈተነ (fatana, “try, test”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32969","headword_ar":"فَتْنٌ","root":"ftn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sort,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobN","text_ar":"ضَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fan~N","text_ar":"فَنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawonN","text_ar":"لَوْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN","text_ar":"حَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, K.) Hence the saying of 'Amr Ibn-Ahmar El-Báhilee,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_im~aA EalaY nafosK waA_im~aA lahaA\n                      \n                     \n                        waAlEayo$u fatonaAni faHulowN wamuro"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Either against a soul or for it; life being of two sorts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conditions, sweet and bitter;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muro","text_ar":"مُرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~N","text_ar":"مُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T; and the latter hemistich, without the incipient"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", is cited in the K;) thus as related by some: but as related by Aboo-Sa'eed [As], he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fan~aAni","text_ar":"فَنَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobaAni","text_ar":"ضَرْبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and as related by Aboo- 'Amr Esh-Sheybánee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonaAni","text_ar":"فِتْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with kesr]; and [he seems to have held that the poet meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two-sided;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] he says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfitonu","text_ar":"الفِتْنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAHiyapu","text_ar":"النَّاحِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfatonaAni","text_ar":"الفَتْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfutonAni","text_ar":"الفُتْنانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) dual of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfatonu","text_ar":"الفَتْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first and last parts of the day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the early part of the morning and the late part of the evening:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) because they are two states, or conditions, and two sorts. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n32970","headword_ar":"فِتْنٌ","root":"ftn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}